 business models, Take-Two is exceedingly well positioned to capitalize on the many positive trends in our industry and to generate growth and margin expansion over the long-term,\u0026rdquo; says Zelnick.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eRecurrent consumer spending (or income sourced from the sale of virtual currency, add-on content, and in-game purchases) increased by 52 percent year-over-year and was ultimately responsible for 58 percent of the quarter\u0026rsquo;s total revenue.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eLike other companies that reaped better-than-expected Q1s, Take-Two Interactive has raised its full-year guidance after just one quarter and now expects to close Fiscal 2021 with GAAP net revenue between $750 million and $800 million and GAAP net income between $98 million and $110 million.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026ldquo;With more people staying at home, we have experienced, and are continuing to experience, heightened levels of engagement and Net Bookings growth-to-date,\u0026rdquo; reads a statement from the company. \u0026ldquo;The full extent of the impact of the COVID-19 pandemic to our business, operations and financial results will depend on numerous evolving factors that we are not able to predict.\u0026rdquo;\u003c/p\u003e","byline":null,"featured_image_caption":null,"featured_image_credit":null,"old_url":"/view/news/367537/TakeTwo_boasts_new_Q1_record_as_revenue_jumps_54_yearoveryear.php","published_date":"2020-08-03T05:00:00.000Z","summary":"Take-Two is reporting record revenue at the close of its first quarter, a milestone no doubt driven by rising consumer recurrent spending and play habits influenced by ongoing pandemic.","term_selector":{"primaryTerm":"console","primaryTermInRealText":"Console","primaryCategoryBelonged":"topics","secondaryTerm":["mobile"]},"title":"Take-Two boasts new Q1 record as revenue jumps 54% year-over-year","url":"/take-two-boasts-new-q1-record-as-revenue-jumps-54-year-over-year","seo":{"meta_title":"Take-Two boasts new Q1 record as revenue jumps 54% year-over-year","meta_description":"Take-Two is reporting record revenue at the close of its first quarter, a milestone no doubt driven by rising consumer recurrent spending and play habits influe","meta_keywords":null,"canonical_url":null,"__typename":"Seo"},"sponsored_content_settings":null,"system":{"uid":"blt686bb9611ba72ce0","updated_at":"2021-08-24T07:58:04.231Z","__typename":"EntrySystemField"},"featured_imageConnection":{"edges":[],"__typename":"SysAssetConnection"},"image_alt_text":null,"__typename":"Article","pageType":"article","featured_image":null,"article_label":[{"title":"News","label":"News","__typename":"ArticleLabel"}],"author_page":[{"title":"Alissa McAloon 2","url":"/author/alissa-mcaloon-2","author_role":"Editor-in-Chief","author_name":"Alissa McAloon","image_alt_text":"Alissa McAloon Headshot","__typename":"Author","portrait":{"url":"https://eu-images.contentstack.com/v3/assets/blt95b381df7c12c15d/blta7dab2863bc69424/610c368ae7abb133f6920c70/Alissa_McAloon.jpg","filename":"Alissa_McAloon.jpg","__typename":"SysAsset"}}],"uid":"blt686bb9611ba72ce0","bodyText":"Take-Two is reporting a sizeable year-over-year increase in revenue at the close of its first quarter, a jump no doubt driven by rising consumer recurrent spending and, as is the case for other companies, play habits influenced by the ongoing COVID-19 pandemic. The company as a whole reported $831.1 million in GAAP net revenue for the quarter ending June 30, a 54 percent increase from the same period the year prior. Net revenue from digital sources made up the bulk of that at $726.2 million for the quarter, up 70 percent from last year\u0026rsquo;s $427.8 million. The usual cast of Take-Two titles are credited with driving this increase, but CEO Strauss Zelnick calls out NBA 2K20, Grand Theft Auto V/Online, Red Dead Redemption 2/Online, and Social Point\u0026rsquo;s mobile games as titles that outperformed expectations and had a particular impact on Q1. \u0026ldquo;With the strongest development pipeline in the history of the company and our ongoing investment in emerging markets, platforms and business models, Take-Two is exceedingly well positioned to capitalize on the many positive trends in our industry and to generate growth and margin expansion over the long-term,\u0026rdquo; says Zelnick. Recurrent consumer spending (or income sourced from the sale of virtual currency, add-on content, and in-game purchases) increased by 52 percent year-over-year and was ultimately responsible for 58 percent of the quarter\u0026rsquo;s total revenue. Like other companies that reaped better-than-expected Q1s, Take-Two Interactive has raised its full-year guidance after just one quarter and now expects to close Fiscal 2021 with GAAP net revenue between $750 million and $800 million and GAAP net income between $98 million and $110 million. \u0026ldquo;With more people staying at home, we have experienced, and are continuing to experience, heightened levels of engagement and Net Bookings growth-to-date,\u0026rdquo; reads a statement from the company. \u0026ldquo;The full extent of the impact of the COVID-19 pandemic to our business, operations and financial results will depend on numerous evolving factors that we are not able to predict.\u0026rdquo;"},"seo":{"meta_title":"Take-Two boasts new Q1 record as revenue jumps 54% year-over-year","meta_description":"Take-Two is reporting record revenue at the close of its first quarter, a milestone no doubt driven by rising consumer recurrent spending and play habits influe","meta_keywords":"","canonical_url":null,"__typename":"Seo"},"slug":"take-two-boasts-new-q1-record-as-revenue-jumps-54-year-over-year","term":{"slug":"topics","display_options":"Standard View","topic_page_description":"","title":"Console","system":{"uid":"blt677a4413e2017e64","__typename":"EntrySystemField"},"seo":{"meta_description":"","canonical_url":"","meta_keywords":"","meta_title":"","__typename":"Seo"},"secon